{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/multiplesizesemantictoken"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleSizeSemanticToken"},"abstract":[{"text":"Kind of semantic tokens which will wrap a combination of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/SizeSemanticToken","type":"reference"},{"text":" depending to viewports \/ size classes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Kind of composite token with multiple values, but not named “composite” because this word is already used in the design system.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Allows to gather the multiple-value tokens from Figma inside one object.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If a size token exists with its value depending to the size class, it must be packed in such ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleSizeSemanticToken","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MultipleSizeSemanticToken","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["        \/\/ Assuming in Figma with have a size semantic token iconWithHeadingXLargeTall,","        \/\/ two semantic size tokens will be defined in Figma and generated by tokenator because","        \/\/ its value can vary if compact or regular modes.","        \/\/ They can be declared in protocol SizeSemanticTokens,","        \/\/ and defined automaticaly in OUDSTheme+SizeSemanticTokens extension","        var iconWithHeadingXLargeTallMobile: SizeSemanticToken { DimensionRawTokens._650 }","        var iconWithHeadingXLargeTallTablet: SizeSemanticToken { DimensionRawTokens._800 }","","        \/\/ Then the develoment team declares an \"higher\" level size semantic token for iconWithHeadingXLargeTall","        \/\/ inside SizeMultipleSemanticTokens protocol,","        \/\/ and defined inside OUDSTheme+SizeMultipleSemanticTokens extension","        var iconWithHeadingXLargeTall: MultipleSizeSemanticToken {","            MultipleSizeSemanticToken(compact: iconWithHeadingXLargeTallMobile, regular: iconWithHeadingXLargeTallTablet)","        }","","        \/\/ If the same value is used whatever the size class is","        var iconWithHeadingXLargeTall: MultipleSizeSemanticToken { MultipleSizeSemanticToken(iconWithHeadingXLargeTallTablet) }","","        \/\/ The theme exposes both generated font size semantic tokens and \"crafted\" higher level color semantic tokens.","        \/\/ It is recommended to use the higher level version as it is less error-prone."]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"0.8.0","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Since"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Class","title":"MultipleSizeSemanticToken","externalID":"c:@M@OUDSTokensSemantic@objc(cs)MultipleSizeSemanticToken","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MultipleSizeSemanticToken","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"class","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"Tokens for semantics"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MultipleSizeSemanticToken","kind":"identifier"}]},"sections":[],"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Inherits From","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/objc(cs)NSObject"],"kind":"relationships","type":"inheritsFrom"},{"title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensS